---
description: Astronomer helm chart base rules
globs:
alwaysApply: true
---

- Always write code that will be easy to refactor.
- Always write code that will be easy for an LLM to refactor.
- All edits should pass pre-commit checks.
- Variables that have the same semantic meaning should be named the same across different files, functions, classes, templates.
- YAML enbedded shell code more than 5 lines should be broken out into a standalone script that lives in bin and is configured with environment variables.
